_________________________________________________________________________________
Now we will be looking at how to write your skills section within your resume. This section will follow your volunteer experience section, which we just learned how to write! Here is the current order for your resume sections:

<img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-44209" src="http://p2i.pyd.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/PYD_resumes3.5-e1515781199456.png" alt="pyd_resumes3-5" width="200" height="232" />
<ol>
 	<li>Heading (personal information)</li>
 	<li>Objective Statement</li>
 	<li>Education</li>
 	<li>Work Experience</li>
 	<li>Volunteer Experience</li>
 	<li><strong>Skills</strong></li>
 	<li><span style="color: #808080;">Optional Sections</span></li>
</ol>
&nbsp;

&nbsp;
<blockquote><strong>Skills</strong> – This section on a resume lists specific career-related things you are good at.</blockquote>
Skills is an optional section on your resume, but one that usually looks good to an employer and is an easy way to tell them what you can contribute to a job.
________________________________________________________________________________
There are two types of skills sets that employers are looking for: <span style="color: #ff0000;">hard</span> and <span style="color: #ff0000;">soft</span>.
<blockquote><strong>Hard Skills</strong> – Specific types of knowledge that allow you to complete your work-related tasks. These skills can be taught to someone and are quantifiable, or able to be measured.</blockquote>
<blockquote><strong>Soft Skills</strong> – Skills that can be applied to a job and are usually people-related. These skills are not quantifiable (cannot be measured) and are harder to teach on the job.</blockquote>
Try to include both in your skill section!

________________________________________________________________________________Now, write your own <strong>Expanded List</strong>! Fill out the information for your previous or current volunteer experiences (in descending chronological order).

Here is the template, now fill in each blank. If you have not volunteered before, think about a volunteer position that you would like to have in the future, and write down the duties you would have!

